NAME
       BERT − BERT serializer/deserializer

SYNOPSIS
         use BERT;

         my $bert = encode_bert([ 1, ’foo’, [ 2, [ 3, 4 ] ], 5 ]);
         my $data = decode_bert($bert);

DESCRIPTION
       This module provides a thin wrapper around BERT::Encoder and
       BERT::Decoder, which converts Perl data structures to BERT format and
       vice versa, respectively.

       See the BERT specification at <http://bert−rpc.org/>.

FUNCTIONS
       $bert = encode_bert($data)
           Returns the BERT representation for the given Perl data structure.
           Croaks on error.

       $data = decode_bert($bert)
           Returns the Perl data structure for the given BERT binary. Croaks
           on error.

